isBinaryName

public static boolean isBinaryName(java.lang.String name)
Parameters:
name - class name to test
Returns:
true if name could be a valid binary name. Note that many invalid names might pass this test -- in particular, source names cannot be verified to know they are not valid binary names without being able to tell the package name part of the name.
